Fourth Department,

October, 1950.

(October 4, 1950.) Louie E. Mead, Appellant, v. Mary W. G. Mead, Respondent.

Order affirmed, with $10 costs and disbursements. All concur. (The appeal is from an order substituting the committee of defendant incompetent as party defendant and requiring plaintiff to submit to examination as to his property and income and to- serve a bill of particulars as to the details of his claim of fraud in an action for an annulment.) Present — Taylor, P. J., McCum, Love, Vaughan and Piper, JJ.
